One station was shut completely as a result of the afternoon glitch. Subway suspended after technical fault One station was shut completely as a result of the afternoon glitch.The inner circle was suspended shortly before 4.00pm on Wednesday afternoon and Kinning Park station in the South Side was closed to all customers &quot;until further notice&quot;, according to transport firm SPT.It is not yet clear how long the service will be out of action for or the reason behind the fault. 